      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Progressive colt MOUNT BARKER BOY (2) has been far too good in winning all three starts since a year on the sidelines, coming from much wider to score by 7m at Geelong last time. Led from this barrier when he won here two back. Takes a step up in grade but can continue to work through his grades. LAMBRO MACH (1) did some work but stuck on to be beaten only 2m last start. He'll relish the ace draw having led from there to win by 7.7m at this circuit and distance two back. KISS ME MINI NZ (5) draws a little wide but has produced some good efforts since coming from the back line to score here in March. IN AN IDEAL WORLD (4) continued his consistent form when he raced parked but stuck on to place last week at Bendigo. He can be competitive again along with DO IT (3) who draws much better than when midfield last week and placed from a similar barrier to this here prior.",
